body:
That may be possible but on my system, it doesn't give any error! 
Using this instead: `rato = tf.cast(tf.equal(sumr, nums), ttyp)` gives correct result but performance is still worse without `tf.Print`:
```
Data Loaded![2 3 4...]
With Dump: found 1229 primes in 13.345328 time
Without Dump: found 1229 primes in 22.766805 time
```
I think it may be because tf.Print somehow forces tensor to load quickly but that's just my assumption.
